<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Inherit entitlements for child processes of the MAS build.

  Electron spawns several helper processes for each window:

    • FileFlow Helper (Renderer)  — the Chromium renderer
    • FileFlow Helper (GPU)       — the GPU process
    • FileFlow Helper (Plugin)    — anything that uses Pepper/PPAPI
    • FileFlow Helper             — the generic helper

  Apple requires each of these to be code-signed and to declare its own
  entitlements. We give the helpers a STRICTLY SMALLER set than the
  main process — only what they need to function — because reviewers
  treat any unnecessary helper-process entitlement as a smell.

  WHY EACH KEY:

    com.apple.security.app-sandbox
        Mandatory for every signed binary in a sandboxed bundle.

    com.apple.security.inherit
        Tells the OS "this child inherits its sandbox profile from the
        parent." Without it, the helper would need a full re-declaration
        of every file/network/IPC entitlement and Apple's auto-checks
        would fail.

    com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
    com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
        The Chromium renderer is V8 — same JIT rationale as the main
        process. Apple's auto-validation knows this is expected for
        Helper (Renderer) and waves it through.

  WHAT'S DELIBERATELY OMITTED:

    com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write
    com.apple.security.files.bookmarks.app-scope
        The renderer NEVER touches files directly — file ops go through
        IPC to the main process, where they're path-allowed-checked
        before any fs call. Granting the renderer file entitlements
        would let a renderer-side compromise escape the IPC chokepoint.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
  <true/>

  <key>com.apple.security.inherit</key>
  <true/>

  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>

  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
